Other Options
In the course we also showcase 2 other ways to achieve the same goal. The first is using group_by and count


dat %>%
  group_by(a) %>% 
  count(b)



or with even shorter code, calling count on both columns we’d like to group by:


dat %>%
  count(a, b)
